Must be a patron of restaurant, but I'm sure they would allow you to go in and use the restroom if you ask. The restaurant is very trans- and NB friendly and is owned by a trans person.
The urinals even have a door on them if you want to try your STP out.

comment:
One gender-neutral single-stall restroom in the Children's Department, Main Level with changing table.
One gender-neutral single-stall restroom on the Upper Floor adjacent Meeting Room 3.
Gendered multistall restrooms on main level.
Both single-stall restrooms and the gendered Ladies restrooms have menstrual products available courtesy Code Red Saint John.

name: Kansas Union - KU
directions:
4th floor of the Kansas Union (street level for Jayhawk Blvd). In the back of the Student Involvement & Leadership Center (SILC). It is back near a number of the offices, near room 422. 
If you enter from Jayhawk Blvd, you will take a right just past the student ambassador desk, just before the stairs. You will then take a left near the Gender & Sexuality center. Depending on which left you take, it will either be on your right, or, you will follow the hallway full of offices in a rectangular U, and it will be on your left on the opposite side of the U.
comment:
It is very small, definitely not accessible, and rather difficult to find. It does have free pads & tampons for those who need them. It also has a needle-disposal container. 
If you are at KU's campus, you can find other gender-inclusive restrooms via this link. 
https://sgd.ku.edu/all-gender-restroom-list
